# _headers — security + caching for static hosts that read this format
# (Netlify, Cloudflare Pages, etc.). The Apache/LiteSpeed equivalent lives in
# .htaccess; this file is the portable counterpart so the same deploy bundle is
# hardened on any of the common static hosts, not only Apache-family ones.
#
# Mirrors .htaccess: long-cache the content-hashed assets, never cache the HTML
# entry point (a stale index.html points at purged hashes — the classic
# white-screen-after-deploy), and the same response-hardening headers, including
# an ENFORCING Content-Security-Policy (matches .htaccess). script-src is strict
# — 'self' plus 'wasm-unsafe-eval' for the laz-perf WASM only; the live bundle
# carries no eval/Function so no 'unsafe-eval' is needed, and there are no inline
# scripts. style-src allows 'unsafe-inline' because the profile chart positions
# its axis labels with inline style attributes; style injection is low-risk and
# no user-derived string reaches the unsafeHtml/innerHTML sinks (enforced by
# `npm run lint:unsafe-html`). worker-src/blob and img blob:/data: cover the
# worker-decoded WASM and generated thumbnails.

/*
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()
  X-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'wasm-unsafe-eval'; worker-src 'self' blob:; connect-src 'self' https:; img-src 'self' blob: data:; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self'

/assets/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

/index.html
  Cache-Control: no-cache
